about.description:
The 'mypy_extensions' module defines experimental extensions to the
standard 'typing' module that are supported by the mypy typechecker.
about.summary: Experimental type system extensions for programs checked with the mypy typechecker.

name: mypy_extensions
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "mypy_extensions" %}
{% set version = "0.4.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: "37e0e956f41369209a3d5f34580150bcacfabaa57b33a15c0b25f4b5725e0812"

build:
  number: 1000
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vvv "

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip

  run:
    - python
    - typing >=3.5.3  # [py<35]

test:
  imports:
    - mypy_extensions

about:
  home: http://www.mypy-lang.org/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  # https://github.com/python/mypy/issues/4247
  # license_file: ''
  summary: Experimental type system extensions for programs checked with the mypy typechecker.
  description: |
      The 'mypy_extensions' module defines experimental extensions to the
      standard 'typing' module that are supported by the mypy typechecker.
  doc_url: https://mypy.readthedocs.io
  dev_url: https://github.com/python/mypy/blob/master/extensions

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nehaljwani
